Inverted Right-Angled Triangle Star Pattern in Java
This Java program prints an inverted right-angled triangle using asterisks (*). 
The triangle starts with n stars in the first row and decreases by one star on each subsequent row until only one star is printed. 
This program is a great exercise for beginners learning nested loops and pattern printing in Java.

import java.util.*;
public class Invertedrighttriangle {

	public static void main(String[] args) {
		// TODO Auto-generated method stub
		Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
		int n = sc.nextInt();
		for(int i=n;i>=1;i--) {
			for(int j=1;j<=i;j++) {
				System.out.print("* ");
				
			}
			System.out.println();
		}

	}

}


Sample Input/Output:
Input:
5
Output:
* * * * * 
* * * * 
* * * 
* * 
* 

Nested for loops for structured output

Decreasing loop logic for inverted patterns

User input handling with Scanner class

Console formatting with System.out.print() and System.out.println()
